==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chorister
<hw>Chor"is*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Chorus</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of a choir; a singer in a
chorus.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who leads a choir in church music.</def>
<mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Choristic</ent>⟦br⟧
